1. ‘Freelancer’ relation-
Attributes: 
(FreelancerID, Name, Email, Bio, HourlyRate, TotalEarnings, Rating, JoinDate) 

Functional Dependencies: 
FreelancerID → Name 
FreelancerID → Email 
FreelancerID → Bio 
FreelancerID → HourlyRate 
FreelancerID → TotalEarnings 
FreelancerID → Rating 
FreelancerID → JoinDate 
Email → FreelancerID 

Proof: 
Let X = FreelancerID 
Closure of X: 
X⁺ = {FreelancerID, Name, Email, Bio, HourlyRate, TotalEarnings, Rating, JoinDate} 
Let Y = Email 
Closure of Y: 
Y⁺ = {Email, FreelancerID, Name, Bio, HourlyRate, TotalEarnings, Rating, JoinDate} 

Hence, FreelancerID and Email are candidate keys. 

All FDs have LHS as candidate keys. 
Therefore, ‘Freelancer’ is in BCNF. 

